               <msContents>
                  <summary>An incomplete copy of <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Nuzhat al-Qulūb</title>
                     (The Adornment of Hearts), a popular medieval cosmography of the world, which
                     <persName key="person_69871519" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/69871519/"
                        xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ḥamd Allāh Mustawfī Qazvīnī (fl.
                        1330-1340)</persName> composed in circa <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                           from="1339" to="1340">740 AH (1339–40 CE)</date>. It commences with an
                     opening (<hi rend="italic">fātiḥah</hi>) with an introduction (<hi
                        rend="italic">muqaddimah</hi>) on the heavens and a preface (<hi
                           rend="italic">dibāchah</hi>) on the inhabited world and its climes, followed
                     by three essays (<hi rend="italic">maqālah</hi>). The first describes the
                     mineral, vegetable and animal kingdoms, the second relates the qualities of
                     humankind, and the third longest portion concerns geography in four sections
                     (<hi rend="italic">qism</hi>) on the holy cities of Mecca, Medina, and
                     Jerusalem, the author's native Iran, neighbouring regions, and foreigns lands.
                     Scholars today still reference the author's vividly detailed descriptions of
                     many cities and regions. This volume regrettably lacks the final page and colophon which would indicate when and where the unidentified scribe completed it.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_927-item1">
                     <author key="person_69871519" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/69871519/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ḥamd Allāh Mustawfī Qazvīnī, fl. 1330–1340
                        </persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">حمد الله مستوفى قزوينى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_483">Nuzhat al-qulūb</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_483">نزهة القلوب</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="basmalla"/>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <note>For another complete copy of this work held in the Rylands, see <ref
                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_6899"><idno>Persian
                           MS 403</idno></ref>. For English translations of the geographical and
                        zoological parts, see Le Strange and Stephenson.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
